WEBVTT

00:00:03.379 --> 00:00:06.424
<i>[Dobie Gray's "Drift Away"]</i>

00:00:10.386 --> 00:00:14.140
Three, three,

00:00:14.223 --> 00:00:19.437
three, three, three,

00:00:19.520 --> 00:00:23.608
four, four, four...

00:00:23.691 --> 00:00:27.153
<i>[singing] You know that's
a game that I hate to lose</i>

00:00:27.236 --> 00:00:28.571
<i>Four...</i>

00:00:28.654 --> 00:00:34.160
five,five,five,

00:00:34.243 --> 00:00:36.370
five, five.

00:00:36.454 --> 00:00:37.663
Okay.

00:00:37.747 --> 00:00:39.415
[distant metal thumping]

00:00:39.498 --> 00:00:41.125
Everyone remember the rules?

00:00:41.209 --> 00:00:43.169
<i>Rock and roll
and drift away</i>

00:00:43.252 --> 00:00:47.173
Are you sure
this is the best idea?

00:00:47.256 --> 00:00:48.925
What else are we gonna do?

00:00:49.008 --> 00:00:51.385
<i>I wanna get lost
in your rock and roll</i>

00:00:51.469 --> 00:00:53.262
<i>And drift away</i>

00:00:53.346 --> 00:00:55.223
Okay, have you got
any eights?

00:00:55.306 --> 00:00:58.392
Uh... go fish.

00:00:59.685 --> 00:01:03.356
<i>[soft brooding music]</i>

00:01:03.439 --> 00:01:05.942
Hey.
It's your turn.

00:01:06.025 --> 00:01:10.196
<i>Think that
I'm wasting time</i>

00:01:10.279 --> 00:01:14.492
Um--um.
Do you have any threes?

00:01:14.575 --> 00:01:17.328
Go fish.

00:01:17.411 --> 00:01:18.663
<i>World outside
is so unkind</i>

00:01:18.746 --> 00:01:21.499
Okay, do you have any...

00:01:21.582 --> 00:01:24.252
The "Resolute" made
23 routine trips.

00:01:24.335 --> 00:01:26.462
So what happened to ours?

00:01:26.545 --> 00:01:28.172
There's no use
in speculating.

00:01:28.256 --> 00:01:30.508
[alarm beeping]

00:01:30.591 --> 00:01:32.593
<i>Completing de-orbit burn.</i>

00:01:32.677 --> 00:01:35.304
Helmets on.

00:01:35.388 --> 00:01:39.141
<i>And drift away
yeah give me the beat...</i>

00:01:39.225 --> 00:01:40.559
<i>Begin entry phase
in 30 seconds.</i>

00:01:40.643 --> 00:01:44.647
[helmets clicking, hissing]

00:01:44.730 --> 00:01:46.440
<i>And drift away</i>

00:01:46.524 --> 00:01:48.609
[sighs]

00:01:48.693 --> 00:01:51.362
Kay, um, it's still my turn.

00:01:57.243 --> 00:01:59.245
Do you have any nines?

00:01:59.328 --> 00:02:01.455
Seriously, Penny?
What?

00:02:01.539 --> 00:02:02.707
Did you see my hand?

00:02:02.790 --> 00:02:04.292
You count cards.

00:02:04.375 --> 00:02:05.584
I don't know
why everyone doesn't.

00:02:05.668 --> 00:02:07.628
Kay, can I have my nine,
please?

00:02:07.712 --> 00:02:10.339
<i>When I'm feelin' blue</i>

00:02:10.423 --> 00:02:12.675
<i>Guitar's comin' through-</i>

00:02:12.758 --> 00:02:14.468
[loud mechanical rumbling]

00:02:14.552 --> 00:02:16.345
[alarms blaring]
<i>Music</i> off.

00:02:16.429 --> 00:02:18.347
<i>Atmospheric disturbance
detected.</i>

00:02:18.431 --> 00:02:20.975
Deep breaths.

00:02:21.058 --> 00:02:23.352
Remember your training.

00:02:23.436 --> 00:02:25.563
The computer will
land us just fine.

00:02:25.646 --> 00:02:26.939
That's what it's for.

00:02:27.023 --> 00:02:28.691
Deep breaths.

00:02:28.774 --> 00:02:31.694
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

00:02:46.584 --> 00:02:49.628
[whooshing]

00:02:52.048 --> 00:02:53.382
[loud clank]

00:02:53.466 --> 00:02:55.301
<i>Impact detected.</i>

00:02:55.384 --> 00:02:58.012
<i>Landing trajectory off course.</i>

00:02:58.095 --> 00:03:00.473
[whimpering]
Mom.

00:03:00.556 --> 00:03:03.726
Take my hand.
It's okay.

00:03:03.809 --> 00:03:05.436
<i>Hold onto me!
Warning.</i>

00:03:05.519 --> 00:03:07.063
<i>Entry angle
exceeding parameters.</i>

00:03:07.146 --> 00:03:08.439
<i>Correcting.</i>

00:03:08.522 --> 00:03:09.982
We're <i>at 4,000</i> feet.
[groans]

00:03:10.066 --> 00:03:11.692
It's okay.
[whimpering]

00:03:11.776 --> 00:03:13.527
<i>3,000 feet.</i>

00:03:13.611 --> 00:03:15.696
<i>Entry angle exceeding
parameters.</i>

00:03:15.780 --> 00:03:17.573
Take my hand.
<i>2,000 feet.</i>

00:03:17.656 --> 00:03:19.533
Take my hand.

00:03:19.617 --> 00:03:21.535
<i>1,000 feet.
Brace for impact.</i>

00:03:21.619 --> 00:03:22.912
<i>Brace for impact.
Brace for impact.</i>

00:03:22.995 --> 00:03:24.038
[booming]

00:03:24.121 --> 00:03:26.457
[pained grunts]

00:03:26.540 --> 00:03:29.460
[rumbling, booming]

00:03:29.543 --> 00:03:30.544
[Yelps]

00:03:30.628 --> 00:03:33.381
[all gasping]

00:03:33.464 --> 00:03:38.469
[alarm blaring]

00:03:38.552 --> 00:03:40.346
Sound off.

00:03:40.429 --> 00:03:41.680
Judy accounted for.

00:03:41.764 --> 00:03:43.557
Penny accounted for.

00:03:43.641 --> 00:03:45.643
[whimpering]

00:03:45.726 --> 00:03:47.269
Will.

00:03:47.353 --> 00:03:48.521
Will!

00:03:48.604 --> 00:03:50.648
Are you all right?
Accounted for.

00:03:50.731 --> 00:03:52.066
[metal screeches]

00:03:52.149 --> 00:03:53.442
<i>Landing surface unstable.</i>

00:03:53.526 --> 00:03:54.527
Let's evacuate.

00:03:54.610 --> 00:03:55.611
Supply cabinet.

00:03:55.694 --> 00:03:56.695
Already on it.

00:03:59.156 --> 00:04:00.950
Maureen.
It's my leg.

00:04:01.033 --> 00:04:02.326
Mom?

00:04:02.410 --> 00:04:03.994
It's fine.
It's just stuck.

00:04:04.078 --> 00:04:05.955
It's okay.
I got this.

00:04:06.038 --> 00:04:07.415
You go get the supplies.

00:04:07.498 --> 00:04:08.624
Will, come on, follow me.

00:04:08.707 --> 00:04:10.501
Damn it!

00:04:11.794 --> 00:04:13.295
[groaning]

00:04:13.379 --> 00:04:14.547
Will, stay close.

00:04:14.630 --> 00:04:16.632
I'm coming.

00:04:16.715 --> 00:04:19.009
Quick, to the top hatch.

00:04:19.093 --> 00:04:20.970
Come on.

00:04:21.053 --> 00:04:23.347
Here, hold on.

00:04:23.431 --> 00:04:26.642
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

00:04:26.725 --> 00:04:29.395
[mechanical whirring]

00:04:29.478 --> 00:04:31.313
[groans]

00:04:31.397 --> 00:04:33.524
[wind howls]

00:04:33.607 --> 00:04:35.025
It's jammed!

00:04:35.109 --> 00:04:37.403
Will, come on up.
Okay.

00:04:37.486 --> 00:04:40.406
<i>Landing surface is unstable.</i>

00:04:42.408 --> 00:04:43.617
Judy!
PIT]

00:04:43.701 --> 00:04:45.411
Come on.

00:04:47.746 --> 00:04:49.665
[suit clanks]

00:04:51.584 --> 00:04:53.669
I--I don't fit.

00:04:53.752 --> 00:04:55.004
We have to go around.

00:04:56.714 --> 00:04:57.965
Don't go anywhere.

00:04:58.048 --> 00:05:00.092
We'll come around.

00:05:03.095 --> 00:05:06.015
<i>[foreboding music]</i>

00:05:11.228 --> 00:05:14.398
[wind howling]

00:05:25.409 --> 00:05:26.452
[grunts]

00:05:29.580 --> 00:05:32.500
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

00:05:44.595 --> 00:05:46.722
Wow.

00:05:46.805 --> 00:05:49.058
[distant booming]

00:05:49.141 --> 00:05:53.145
[ships whooshing]

00:06:01.612 --> 00:06:03.572
[sighs]

00:06:05.783 --> 00:06:08.160
Are those other Jupiters?

00:06:08.244 --> 00:06:09.995
At least eight.

00:06:10.079 --> 00:06:13.582
We're not the only ones
that made it.

00:06:13.666 --> 00:06:15.709
Made it where?

00:06:15.793 --> 00:06:18.420
Here, sit down.

00:06:20.089 --> 00:06:21.173
Ah...

00:06:21.257 --> 00:06:23.676
Lucky, I just happened
to be here.

00:06:23.759 --> 00:06:25.052
Lucky thing.

00:06:25.135 --> 00:06:27.471
[ice cracking]

00:06:27.555 --> 00:06:28.681
[rumbling]

00:06:28.764 --> 00:06:31.141
No,no,no!

00:06:35.688 --> 00:06:37.147
[metal creaking]

00:06:37.231 --> 00:06:40.150
<i>[foreboding music]</i>

00:06:54.039 --> 00:06:57.626
<i>[Dean Martin's "Let It Snow"]</i>

00:06:57.710 --> 00:06:59.128
<i>So, who's
my Secret Santa?</i>

00:06:59.211 --> 00:07:01.171
<i>[singing] ls so delightful...</i>

00:07:01.255 --> 00:07:03.007
[scoffs]

00:07:03.090 --> 00:07:05.217
<i>Place to go</i>

00:07:05.301 --> 00:07:06.677
<i>Let it snow
let it snow let it snow</i>

00:07:06.760 --> 00:07:08.178
Ta-da.

00:07:08.262 --> 00:07:09.722
<i>Are those my mom's cookies?</i>

00:07:09.805 --> 00:07:11.098
Grandma wasn't here
to bake them this year,

00:07:11.181 --> 00:07:13.017
so, gave it a shot.

00:07:13.100 --> 00:07:14.602
<i>She never trusted me
with the recipe.</i>

00:07:14.685 --> 00:07:16.979
I don't know,
I guess I'm just special.

00:07:17.062 --> 00:07:18.981
<i>[laughs]</i>

00:07:19.064 --> 00:07:21.692
So, where are you
these days?

00:07:21.775 --> 00:07:23.611
You know he can't say.

00:07:23.694 --> 00:07:26.655
Well, wherever you are,
it's night.

00:07:26.739 --> 00:07:28.949
Which rules out Europe,

00:07:29.033 --> 00:07:31.577
Africa, the Middle East,

00:07:31.744 --> 00:07:34.079
Asia, Australia--

00:07:34.163 --> 00:07:35.497
Is that our hedge?

00:07:38.042 --> 00:07:39.209
<i>[laughs]</i>

00:07:39.293 --> 00:07:40.961
What?

00:07:41.045 --> 00:07:43.464
<i>You guys are too smart.</i>

00:07:43.547 --> 00:07:46.258
[door lock clinks]

00:07:46.342 --> 00:07:47.551
[gasps]
Dad!

00:07:47.635 --> 00:07:49.470
<i>[gentle music]</i>

00:07:49.553 --> 00:07:50.929
I missed you!
flaughs]

00:07:51.013 --> 00:07:53.223
You're home!
Oh, my God.

00:07:53.307 --> 00:07:55.017
Let me in.

00:07:57.519 --> 00:07:59.730
Ew, you guys...
Gross.

00:07:59.813 --> 00:08:01.482
Get a room.

00:08:02.775 --> 00:08:05.611
What did you bring me?
flaughs]

00:08:07.029 --> 00:08:10.032
You know how many strings
I had to pull to get here?

00:08:12.284 --> 00:08:14.662
[phone beeps]

00:08:14.745 --> 00:08:18.123
[phone vibrating]

00:08:18.207 --> 00:08:20.668
Hello?

00:08:20.751 --> 00:08:23.003
What?

00:08:23.087 --> 00:08:25.089
When?

00:08:25.172 --> 00:08:27.591
<i>Astronomers at the
Near-Earth Object office</i>

00:08:27.675 --> 00:08:30.636
<i>discovered a sizable,
unknown celestial object</i>

00:08:30.719 --> 00:08:31.929
<i>that's headed our way.</i>

00:08:32.012 --> 00:08:33.514
<i>NASA scientists are working</i>

00:08:33.597 --> 00:08:35.265
<i>around the clock
to track the object's</i>

00:08:35.349 --> 00:08:37.226
<i>orbital path and to
assess the risk of collision.</i>

00:08:37.309 --> 00:08:38.310
lhaveit

00:08:38.394 --> 00:08:40.020
<i>A news briefing
has been scheduled--</i>

00:08:41.271 --> 00:08:42.731
I'm gonna take a look,
okay, Mom?

00:08:43.023 --> 00:08:45.984
Mm-hmm.
[pained gasp]

00:08:46.068 --> 00:08:47.569
It's broken.

00:08:47.653 --> 00:08:50.114
Well, that's too bad.

00:08:52.658 --> 00:08:54.952
Hey, you took time
to grab that?

00:08:55.035 --> 00:08:56.578
Who are you planning to call?
I grabbed a pack.

00:08:56.662 --> 00:08:57.955
I did what
I was supposed to do.

00:08:58.038 --> 00:08:59.039
Hey, kids.

00:08:59.123 --> 00:09:00.124
Could be worse.

00:09:00.207 --> 00:09:01.500
<i>How'?</i>

00:09:01.583 --> 00:09:03.168
<i>[soft music]</i>

00:09:03.252 --> 00:09:04.962
Mom!

00:09:05.045 --> 00:09:06.213
Hey--hey--hey,
what are you doing?

00:09:06.296 --> 00:09:08.507
We haven't tested
the atmosphere.

00:09:08.590 --> 00:09:10.592
[inhales] You already did.

00:09:11.927 --> 00:09:12.928
Look.

00:09:13.011 --> 00:09:15.222
If the air was toxic
you'd be dead by now.

00:09:16.265 --> 00:09:17.266
[sighs]

00:09:21.145 --> 00:09:22.688
[breathes deeply]

00:09:22.771 --> 00:09:24.231
[breathes deeply]

00:09:24.314 --> 00:09:27.151
Not a bad consolation prize.

00:09:27.234 --> 00:09:29.695
First fresh air in months.

00:09:32.281 --> 00:09:34.158
[flare booms]

00:09:35.367 --> 00:09:37.244
[soft hissing]

00:09:42.416 --> 00:09:44.585
[radio clicks]
Mayday, mayday.

00:09:44.668 --> 00:09:46.211
This is "Jupiter 2."
Do you read?

00:09:46.295 --> 00:09:47.337
Over.
[radio clicks]

00:09:52.050 --> 00:09:54.094
Probably should have read
the fine print

00:09:54.178 --> 00:09:57.055
before I launched into space.

00:09:57.139 --> 00:09:58.891
<i>Okay, let's figure out
where we are.</i>

00:09:59.141 --> 00:10:01.643
We evacuated
the "Resolute" halfway between

00:10:01.727 --> 00:10:03.729
home and the colony--
Just call it Earth.

00:10:03.812 --> 00:10:06.064
It's not your home anymore.

00:10:06.148 --> 00:10:08.776
Earth and the colony.

00:10:09.067 --> 00:10:11.361
This planet is unlike
any we have ever mapped.

00:10:11.445 --> 00:10:13.197
Wherever we are, I--

00:10:13.280 --> 00:10:14.323
It's a Goldilocks planet.

00:10:14.406 --> 00:10:15.699
Earth-like atmosphere,

00:10:15.783 --> 00:10:17.242
air pressure, gravity,

00:10:17.326 --> 00:10:19.244
clearly no lack of water.

00:10:19.328 --> 00:10:20.662
It's...

00:10:20.746 --> 00:10:23.624
The odds of
that happening are...

00:10:23.707 --> 00:10:25.250
It's--it's like
winning the lottery.

00:10:25.334 --> 00:10:26.710
Why not dying in
a car accident?

00:10:26.794 --> 00:10:28.212
It's like winning the lottery.

00:10:28.295 --> 00:10:30.964
Till you remember you're
in a car accident.

00:10:31.048 --> 00:10:33.425
We're lost.
No kidding.

00:10:37.054 --> 00:10:40.933
I can't raise any
of the other Jupiters.

00:10:41.016 --> 00:10:43.393
"Resolute" will send
a rescue party. Right?

00:10:43.477 --> 00:10:46.355
I'm sure they'll follow
emergency protocol.

00:10:46.438 --> 00:10:48.106
Hey, where does it hurt?

00:10:48.190 --> 00:10:49.691
All across here.

00:10:49.775 --> 00:10:51.693
It's from the crash harness.
It's normal.

00:10:51.777 --> 00:10:53.362
To you, maybe, not to him.

00:10:53.445 --> 00:10:54.696
He didn't
mean anything by it.

00:10:54.780 --> 00:10:56.031
Yeah, maybe he just forgot

00:10:56.114 --> 00:10:57.115
we're not under his command.

00:10:58.033 --> 00:10:59.743
It's okay.

00:11:00.494 --> 00:11:01.995
Here, ready?

00:11:02.079 --> 00:11:03.664
Inhale.
[inhales]

00:11:03.747 --> 00:11:05.374
Hold.

00:11:06.375 --> 00:11:08.001
[both exhale]

00:11:08.126 --> 00:11:09.169
[distant rumbling]

00:11:09.253 --> 00:11:10.796
[all gasp]

00:11:13.757 --> 00:11:15.717
Is that another crashed ship?

00:11:15.801 --> 00:11:17.970
You're disappointing me.
Look at the color.

00:11:18.053 --> 00:11:19.388
It's bright white...

00:11:19.471 --> 00:11:21.181
If it was rocket fuel,
it would be reddish.

00:11:21.265 --> 00:11:22.933
Right.

00:11:23.016 --> 00:11:25.060
Okay, hint.
It's not a chemistry question.

00:11:25.143 --> 00:11:26.395
It's a geology question.

00:11:26.478 --> 00:11:29.314
[distant rumbling]

00:11:31.483 --> 00:11:33.193
Once that water freezes
the "Jupiter's"

00:11:33.277 --> 00:11:36.321
gonna be locked in
50 feet of solid ice.

00:11:36.405 --> 00:11:38.365
How long do we have?
A while.

00:11:38.448 --> 00:11:41.326
How long is a while?
It depends...

00:11:41.410 --> 00:11:44.037
on hull thermodynamics,
water salinity,

00:11:44.121 --> 00:11:45.163
how much displacement
there is.

00:11:45.247 --> 00:11:46.331
It's complicated.

00:11:46.415 --> 00:11:48.166
Does it matter?
You tell me.

00:11:48.250 --> 00:11:52.045
I know you've already done
the calculations.

00:11:52.129 --> 00:11:53.297
We should talk about
this privately.

00:11:53.380 --> 00:11:56.091
Do you two mind
letting us in on this?

00:11:56.174 --> 00:11:58.343
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

00:12:03.348 --> 00:12:06.226
In six hours,
the sun's gonna go down

00:12:06.310 --> 00:12:10.230
and indications are it will
drop to 60 degrees below 0.

00:12:10.314 --> 00:12:12.190
At which point
our power cells will die--

00:12:12.274 --> 00:12:14.943
And so will we.

00:12:15.027 --> 00:12:16.695
We can't go anywhere
because of your leg.

00:12:16.778 --> 00:12:18.196
I am still figuring it out.

00:12:18.280 --> 00:12:20.115
What if you can't?
Then you leave me here.

00:12:20.198 --> 00:12:22.451
You descend the glacier and
it'll be warmer down there.

00:12:22.534 --> 00:12:23.702
Mom, stop.
No, Mom.

00:12:23.785 --> 00:12:27.664
There's another way.

00:12:27.748 --> 00:12:28.957
We go back down.

00:12:29.041 --> 00:12:30.042
Get one of
the big ion lithiums

00:12:30.125 --> 00:12:31.209
to recharge the suits.

00:12:31.293 --> 00:12:32.461
Not with that
tear in your suit.

00:12:32.544 --> 00:12:34.463
Airlock's too far.
You'll be dead in minutes.

00:12:34.546 --> 00:12:37.341
The broken top hatch.

00:12:37.424 --> 00:12:39.384
It's closer.

00:12:43.055 --> 00:12:44.264
It'll only be a quick trip
in and out.

00:12:44.348 --> 00:12:46.224
He's the only one who'll fit.

00:12:46.308 --> 00:12:47.684
No, absolutely not.

00:12:47.851 --> 00:12:50.020
He did the same training,
passed the same tests.

00:12:50.103 --> 00:12:51.229
You can't train for this.

00:12:51.313 --> 00:12:53.440
Actually, you can.
And he did.

00:12:53.523 --> 00:12:54.524
Will.
John!

00:12:54.608 --> 00:12:56.360
Come with me.
Come on.

00:12:56.443 --> 00:12:58.153
John!

00:12:58.236 --> 00:13:00.364
You're okay.
You got to listen to me.

00:13:00.447 --> 00:13:02.282
All you have to do
is go back in

00:13:02.366 --> 00:13:05.452
the same way you came out.
Supplies room's right there.

00:13:05.535 --> 00:13:07.204
It's easy.

00:13:07.287 --> 00:13:08.330
Kay?

00:13:08.413 --> 00:13:11.375
Take your jacket off.

00:13:11.458 --> 00:13:13.460
Okay.

00:13:13.543 --> 00:13:15.379
Hey-hey, buddy-

00:13:15.462 --> 00:13:17.130
It's no different from
the EVA tank training

00:13:17.214 --> 00:13:19.967
you did back home, kay?

00:13:20.050 --> 00:13:22.094
I'm gonna get the suit.

00:13:24.429 --> 00:13:27.265
<i>[foreboding music]</i>

00:13:29.017 --> 00:13:30.560
Okay.
Here we go.

00:13:30.644 --> 00:13:32.562
Let's put this back on.

00:13:32.646 --> 00:13:34.940
[groans]

00:13:35.023 --> 00:13:37.234
I got this, squirt.
Judy.

00:13:46.410 --> 00:13:49.204
Judy.
Get back up here right now.

00:13:51.081 --> 00:13:53.667
<i>You know you won't
fit through the top hatch.</i>

00:13:54.042 --> 00:13:55.419
[deep breath]

00:13:55.502 --> 00:13:58.422
The top hatch isn't
the only way in, Dad.

00:13:58.505 --> 00:14:01.049
The supply room is too far
from the aft air-lock.

00:14:01.299 --> 00:14:03.593
<i>It's too risky.</i>

00:14:03.677 --> 00:14:05.846
You take risks for
a living, Dad.

00:14:05.971 --> 00:14:09.182
<i>No, I take orders, and
I'm giving you one right now.</i>

00:14:09.391 --> 00:14:11.560
<i>I'm already in.</i>

00:14:11.643 --> 00:14:14.021
[soft laugh]

00:14:14.104 --> 00:14:17.024
Listen to me.
She's gonna be okay.

00:14:17.107 --> 00:14:18.358
Okay, she's always okay.

00:14:18.442 --> 00:14:20.902
It's actually...
really annoying.

00:14:26.658 --> 00:14:28.577
[grunts]

00:14:29.619 --> 00:14:31.079
[metal thuds]

00:14:31.163 --> 00:14:33.540
[grunting]

00:14:35.042 --> 00:14:36.960
The bulkhead's jammed.
I can't get through.

00:14:37.210 --> 00:14:39.463
Okay well, that settles it.
Get back up here right now.

00:14:45.510 --> 00:14:47.471
I can make it.

00:14:48.305 --> 00:14:50.307
[grunts]

00:14:55.645 --> 00:14:57.397
Damn it.

00:14:57.481 --> 00:14:59.524
Honey, I don't know
when the water's gonna freeze.

00:15:01.568 --> 00:15:03.445
I'm fine.

00:15:06.198 --> 00:15:07.574
[grunts]

00:15:10.577 --> 00:15:13.080
[sighs]

00:15:20.212 --> 00:15:21.838
Hey, Judy.

00:15:22.172 --> 00:15:24.508
<i>Judy, why can't
we see you by now?</i>

00:15:27.552 --> 00:15:29.012
<i>Judy?</i>

00:15:29.096 --> 00:15:30.138
Took a chariot battery.

00:15:31.181 --> 00:15:33.100
You're down in the garage?

00:15:33.183 --> 00:15:34.226
[ice splintering]

00:15:34.309 --> 00:15:36.520
<i>Get out of there right now!</i>

00:15:36.603 --> 00:15:37.646
Yeah, good idea.

00:15:38.563 --> 00:15:40.524
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

00:15:40.607 --> 00:15:43.360
Judy, hurry up.

00:15:43.443 --> 00:15:44.611
Faster.

00:15:44.694 --> 00:15:46.154
<i>Move.</i>

00:15:48.490 --> 00:15:49.491
Hurry!

00:15:51.868 --> 00:15:52.869
Come on, Judy.

00:15:57.332 --> 00:15:58.458
Drop the battery.

00:15:58.542 --> 00:16:00.252
<i>Drop the battery!</i>

00:16:02.712 --> 00:16:06.174
[grunting]

00:16:07.717 --> 00:16:09.302
Take my hand!

00:16:10.762 --> 00:16:12.556
[grunts]

00:16:12.639 --> 00:16:14.349
[grunting]

00:16:17.686 --> 00:16:19.146
Damn it!

00:16:19.229 --> 00:16:20.355
[ice hardens]

00:16:20.438 --> 00:16:22.315
<i>[panicked breaths]</i>

00:16:22.399 --> 00:16:24.109
<i>I--I can't move!</i>

00:16:24.192 --> 00:16:26.194
<i>Get me out of here!
Get me out--get me out!</i>

00:16:26.278 --> 00:16:27.529
<i>Get me out--
[panicked breaths]</i>

00:16:27.612 --> 00:16:29.364
Okay. Okay.

00:16:29.447 --> 00:16:30.615
<i>Okay, listen.</i>

00:16:31.616 --> 00:16:34.119
Control your breathing.

00:16:34.369 --> 00:16:36.538
[deep breaths]

00:16:36.621 --> 00:16:38.290
Penny, get the computer.

00:16:38.373 --> 00:16:40.333
I can break through it.

00:16:40.500 --> 00:16:43.128
It's gonna be okay.

00:16:43.211 --> 00:16:46.464
Your suit will keep
you warm and--

00:16:48.383 --> 00:16:50.427
You've got at
least five hours of oxygen.

00:16:50.510 --> 00:16:52.262
Okay.

00:16:52.345 --> 00:16:54.556
<i>Just don't talk any more
than you have to, okay?</i>

00:16:58.393 --> 00:17:00.353
Mm.

00:17:04.608 --> 00:17:06.484
Hey.

00:17:06.568 --> 00:17:08.486
You're in worse shape
than you look.

00:17:09.529 --> 00:17:11.156
Is that a compliment?

00:17:11.239 --> 00:17:13.074
You need to get some rest.

00:17:13.158 --> 00:17:14.492
I need to help my baby girl.

00:17:14.576 --> 00:17:16.745
We Will.
We Will.

00:17:20.248 --> 00:17:22.375
[pained moans]

00:17:23.543 --> 00:17:26.379
No more doing anything
until I say so.

00:17:28.381 --> 00:17:31.092
[pained sighs]

00:17:31.176 --> 00:17:32.719
Maureen?

00:17:34.346 --> 00:17:36.473
Maureen.

00:17:38.266 --> 00:17:39.935
Is she okay?

00:17:40.018 --> 00:17:42.103
Dad?
It's okay.

00:17:42.187 --> 00:17:43.688
It's okay.
She's just resting.

00:17:47.275 --> 00:17:48.276
It's okay.

00:17:48.443 --> 00:17:50.654
[radio beeps]
Judy.

00:17:51.488 --> 00:17:52.530
<i>Judy, I just want to</i> say--

00:17:52.614 --> 00:17:54.616
Don't talk to me, please.

00:17:57.577 --> 00:18:00.497
<i>[forlorn music]</i>

00:18:04.584 --> 00:18:07.337
[grunting]

00:18:14.261 --> 00:18:16.513
You're almost to me, right?

00:18:16.596 --> 00:18:19.557
[panting]

00:18:20.642 --> 00:18:23.770
Yeah, I'm...
I'm getting there.

00:18:25.647 --> 00:18:27.941
[panting]

00:18:28.275 --> 00:18:30.151
[grunting]

00:18:30.235 --> 00:18:33.071
[distant rumble]

00:18:38.493 --> 00:18:41.788
[ice chipping]

00:18:47.585 --> 00:18:50.213
[panting]

00:18:51.339 --> 00:18:53.633
What is it?

00:18:53.717 --> 00:18:55.677
The white fire.

00:18:55.760 --> 00:18:56.845
I figured out what it is.

00:18:57.387 --> 00:18:58.430
I don't have time for this.

00:18:59.472 --> 00:19:00.682
[grunting]

00:19:00.765 --> 00:19:02.726
I mean, when we crashed,

00:19:02.809 --> 00:19:05.562
we must have scraped open
a pure vein of it.

00:19:05.645 --> 00:19:06.688
Vein of what?

00:19:06.771 --> 00:19:08.773
Magnesium.

00:19:10.358 --> 00:19:12.610
Magnesium burns hot.

00:19:12.694 --> 00:19:15.488
But you know what makes
it burn hotter?

00:19:17.532 --> 00:19:19.576
Ice.

00:19:22.579 --> 00:19:25.623
Judy,I got
to go get something.

00:19:25.707 --> 00:19:27.625
You're <i>leaving?
It'll help get you out.</i>

00:19:27.709 --> 00:19:29.461
I'll be back.

00:19:32.255 --> 00:19:35.216
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

00:19:41.306 --> 00:19:42.932
You're gonna have
to hold down the fort.

00:19:43.141 --> 00:19:45.226
It's actually more
of a tent, but--

00:19:45.310 --> 00:19:46.436
You'll be fine.
Just radio me

00:19:46.519 --> 00:19:48.646
if anything goes wrong.

00:19:50.690 --> 00:19:52.359
Are you coming?

00:19:54.027 --> 00:19:56.446
Me?
Yeah, it's your idea.

00:19:56.529 --> 00:19:58.114
And I don't know
what I'm looking for.

00:19:58.406 --> 00:20:00.575
Come on.

00:20:04.412 --> 00:20:06.289
See you later, okay?

00:20:07.624 --> 00:20:10.543
<i>[uplifting orchestral music]</i>

00:20:13.630 --> 00:20:15.006
[kisses]

00:20:25.308 --> 00:20:28.228
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

00:20:36.945 --> 00:20:39.697
[distant sirens wailing]

00:20:45.578 --> 00:20:48.623
[holiday Muzak playing]

00:20:55.588 --> 00:20:57.632
Hi, can I look
at this one please?

00:20:57.715 --> 00:20:59.008
Thank you.

00:21:03.471 --> 00:21:05.432
It--it looks really
expensive.

00:21:05.515 --> 00:21:07.058
Mom, it's babysitting money.

00:21:07.142 --> 00:21:09.394
All right, it's like
being paid to study.

00:21:09.602 --> 00:21:11.104
And I know we're not
doing Secret Santa

00:21:11.187 --> 00:21:12.355
but I want to
get a gift for Dad

00:21:12.439 --> 00:21:14.607
in case he shows up.

00:21:15.650 --> 00:21:17.360
He's done it before.

00:21:17.444 --> 00:21:19.612
Well, I just don't want
you to be disappointed again.

00:21:19.696 --> 00:21:24.284
Well, it's a good thing
I've got thick skin.

00:21:24.367 --> 00:21:27.537
Shouldn't have
to have thick skin.

00:21:27.620 --> 00:21:30.123
He's been in the worst of it
for three years.

00:21:30.206 --> 00:21:33.960
Mom, he's made sacrifices,
so should we.

00:21:34.043 --> 00:21:35.295
Can I take that please?

00:21:35.378 --> 00:21:37.297
Oh, here,
I'll put it on the card.

00:21:37.380 --> 00:21:40.383
Just for the points. You can
pay me when I get the bill.

00:21:40.467 --> 00:21:42.427
Sure. Okay.

00:21:43.553 --> 00:21:46.306
How easy is it
to return this?

00:21:46.389 --> 00:21:49.517
It's fine. As long as
it hasn't been worn.

00:21:49.601 --> 00:21:51.060
It won't be.

00:21:51.144 --> 00:21:54.647
Hey, Mom, I'm gonna go
find a present for Judy.

00:21:54.731 --> 00:21:56.357
She told me to give
it to charity

00:21:56.441 --> 00:21:58.234
but she's just trying
to make me look bad.

00:21:58.485 --> 00:22:01.488
[grunting]

00:22:06.493 --> 00:22:08.077
[groans]

00:22:09.078 --> 00:22:10.079
How's Mom?

00:22:11.080 --> 00:22:12.582
I thought you weren't
supposed to be talking.

00:22:12.665 --> 00:22:14.751
Yeah, you'd like that,
wouldn't you?

00:22:17.795 --> 00:22:20.673
Seriously, how is she?

00:22:20.757 --> 00:22:23.551
<i>She's--she's still out.</i>

00:22:23.676 --> 00:22:27.388
Breathing and her heart rate
is normal.

00:22:29.766 --> 00:22:31.643
Keep talking.

00:22:31.726 --> 00:22:33.102
Pretty high up on the list

00:22:33.186 --> 00:22:34.812
of things I never thought
I'd hear you say.

00:22:35.063 --> 00:22:37.315
Well, you must have some
books loaded on your phone.

00:22:38.483 --> 00:22:40.568
<i>Do you have anything good?</i>

00:22:40.652 --> 00:22:43.446
I, in fact, happen to have

00:22:43.530 --> 00:22:45.990
some of the best books
ever written.

00:22:46.157 --> 00:22:50.161
<i>Complete Dickens,
complete Shakespeare--</i>

00:22:50.245 --> 00:22:53.456
Do you have anything...

00:22:53.540 --> 00:22:54.707
trashy?

00:22:55.458 --> 00:22:58.336
Why would I bring something
trashy to the new world?

00:22:58.461 --> 00:23:00.171
We're here
to establish a colony

00:23:00.255 --> 00:23:02.465
to expand the bounds
of human experience.

00:23:02.632 --> 00:23:04.175
Hmm.

00:23:04.259 --> 00:23:05.635
Well, they say
everyone should read

00:23:05.718 --> 00:23:07.178
"Moby-Dick" before they die.

00:23:10.473 --> 00:23:12.392
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

00:23:12.475 --> 00:23:14.060
Don't say that.

00:23:14.227 --> 00:23:16.062
Oh, do you have it?

00:23:17.146 --> 00:23:19.023
Of course I have it.

00:23:19.107 --> 00:23:21.526
<i>Well, is it any good?</i>

00:23:25.488 --> 00:23:27.156
I don't know.

00:23:27.240 --> 00:23:30.076
Um, I haven't
gotten to the "M's" yet.

00:23:31.286 --> 00:23:33.788
Well, proceed.

00:23:44.173 --> 00:23:46.009
"Call me Ishmael."
Okay...

00:23:46.175 --> 00:23:47.844
<i>Ishmael, if you insist.</i>

00:23:48.094 --> 00:23:51.097
Okay, first of all, that
wasn't even remotely funny,

00:23:51.180 --> 00:23:54.767
and secondly, you're supposed
to be conserving oxygen.

00:23:55.059 --> 00:23:58.563
<i>So, quiet.</i>

00:23:58.646 --> 00:24:02.525
<i>"Call me Ishmael.</i>

00:24:02.609 --> 00:24:05.445
<i>"Some years ago, never mind
how long precisely..."</i>

00:24:05.612 --> 00:24:08.531
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

00:24:15.622 --> 00:24:16.956
Just follow my lead.

00:24:17.040 --> 00:24:19.542
I'm not sure
how stable this glacier is.

00:24:19.626 --> 00:24:21.502
Don't want to fall down
a crevasse.

00:24:21.586 --> 00:24:24.714
Wait--wait,
that could happen?

00:24:24.797 --> 00:24:27.508
Just follow my lead.

00:24:30.094 --> 00:24:32.263
So, uh...

00:24:32.347 --> 00:24:34.724
So, what are
you into nowadays?

00:24:35.016 --> 00:24:36.726
I mean, besides magnesium.

00:24:36.809 --> 00:24:39.062
I'm--I'm not.

00:24:39.145 --> 00:24:41.981
I just ended up testing
into the geology program.

00:24:42.190 --> 00:24:44.275
Yeah, well, they do that.

00:24:44.359 --> 00:24:47.528
You're good at something,
they make you do it.

00:24:49.280 --> 00:24:52.241
I remember you used to
like baseball.

00:24:52.325 --> 00:24:54.160
Yeah.

00:24:56.287 --> 00:24:58.289
Yeah, I used to.

00:24:58.373 --> 00:25:00.458
Models?

00:25:00.541 --> 00:25:03.461
Does anyone
make models anymore?

00:25:03.544 --> 00:25:05.630
I like to read.

00:25:05.713 --> 00:25:07.256
[chuckles]

00:25:07.340 --> 00:25:08.716
Jeez, I don't think
I've read anything

00:25:08.800 --> 00:25:13.262
except instruction manuals
for... years.

00:25:17.100 --> 00:25:20.019
<i>[Uplifting music]</i>

00:25:22.146 --> 00:25:24.023
Oh, damn.

00:25:24.107 --> 00:25:25.274
Yeah...

00:25:25.358 --> 00:25:28.528
That--
that's a lot of magnesium.

00:25:28.611 --> 00:25:31.197
Uh-huh.

00:25:31.280 --> 00:25:34.992
What do you say we go get
some that isn't burning?

00:25:35.076 --> 00:25:36.786
Come on.

00:25:49.674 --> 00:25:51.718
<i>"Fell into their shaggy
watch coats.</i>

00:25:51.801 --> 00:25:53.594
<i>And with their heads muffled
in woolen--"</i>

00:25:53.678 --> 00:25:54.679
<i>Penny!</i>

00:25:55.638 --> 00:25:57.598
What?
Mom.

00:25:57.682 --> 00:25:59.225
Mom, easy.

00:25:59.308 --> 00:26:01.102
Easy. Easy--easy--ea$Y-
[pained gasp]

00:26:01.185 --> 00:26:02.603
Where's Will?

00:26:02.687 --> 00:26:04.439
He went with Dad
to get some magnesium.

00:26:05.106 --> 00:26:06.649
What?

00:26:06.733 --> 00:26:08.276
[scoffs]

00:26:08.359 --> 00:26:11.195
Whose idea was that?

00:26:11.279 --> 00:26:13.156
Will's.

00:26:13.239 --> 00:26:15.116
[wind whooshing]

00:26:16.701 --> 00:26:18.077
What are we looking for?

00:26:19.245 --> 00:26:21.539
It's that grayish
stuff there.

00:26:22.665 --> 00:26:25.334
[distant rumbling]

00:26:25.793 --> 00:26:28.504
That's what it looks like
before it ignites.

00:26:28.588 --> 00:26:30.590
Hey, I'm...

00:26:30.673 --> 00:26:34.093
I'm not gonna blow us up,
am I?

00:26:34.177 --> 00:26:37.930
Not unless you make a spark.

00:26:38.014 --> 00:26:40.308
<i>KEY-</i>

00:26:44.228 --> 00:26:46.105
[grunts]

00:26:47.273 --> 00:26:48.316
How long have we been gone?

00:26:48.858 --> 00:26:50.234
Judy's got plenty of time.

00:26:55.239 --> 00:26:56.949
Hey.

00:26:57.033 --> 00:26:59.243
Ithappened.

00:26:59.327 --> 00:27:01.662
It happened because
I froze up.

00:27:01.746 --> 00:27:03.289
You jumped through
a lot of hoops

00:27:03.372 --> 00:27:05.625
to get on this mission.

00:27:05.708 --> 00:27:07.168
You earned your spot

00:27:07.251 --> 00:27:08.586
just like everyone else.

00:27:08.669 --> 00:27:10.671
I don't feel like
everyone else.

00:27:14.467 --> 00:27:18.012
<i>[soft music]</i>

00:27:18.262 --> 00:27:20.389
I think we've got enough
to get her out

00:27:20.473 --> 00:27:22.391
Now let's get out of here
before it blows up.

00:27:22.475 --> 00:27:23.768
[ice crashing]

00:27:24.101 --> 00:27:25.144
[screaming]

00:27:25.311 --> 00:27:26.562
[grunting]

00:27:26.646 --> 00:27:27.688
Will!
[screaming]

00:27:27.772 --> 00:27:29.565
Will!
Will!

00:27:29.649 --> 00:27:32.151
[screaming]

00:27:32.235 --> 00:27:35.196
[grunting]

00:27:35.279 --> 00:27:36.322
[screams]

00:27:38.366 --> 00:27:40.284
[grunts]

00:27:40.368 --> 00:27:43.079
[radio clicks]
Will. Do you read me?

00:27:43.162 --> 00:27:44.789
Will!

00:27:49.752 --> 00:27:51.420
Mm-hmm.
Uh-huh.

00:27:51.504 --> 00:27:54.006
Okay.

00:27:54.090 --> 00:27:55.424
Ahh!

00:27:55.508 --> 00:27:58.177
It's getting worse,
isn't it?

00:27:58.261 --> 00:28:00.471
Feels like
my leg is in a vice.

00:28:00.680 --> 00:28:03.182
<i>[breathes deeply]</i>

00:28:03.266 --> 00:28:05.351
Penny, I think
we should take a look.

00:28:06.519 --> 00:28:07.937
"We"?

00:28:08.020 --> 00:28:09.355
Does the skin
feel hard or soft?

00:28:09.438 --> 00:28:11.274
Ahh.

00:28:17.738 --> 00:28:19.490
[pained groaning]
Oh yeah.

00:28:19.699 --> 00:28:22.451
<i>Yeah, her leg is hard
as a rock.</i>

00:28:22.535 --> 00:28:25.079
Mom, I think you have
compartment syndrome.

00:28:25.454 --> 00:28:27.957
<i>Edema from the fracture
has created too much pressure</i>

00:28:28.040 --> 00:28:29.500
<i>in your leg.
We have to release it.</i>

00:28:29.709 --> 00:28:32.044
<i>Penny, gonna have to do
a little procedure, okay?</i>

00:28:32.253 --> 00:28:33.296
Uh, no, she's not.

00:28:33.379 --> 00:28:34.422
<i>I'll talk her through it.</i>

00:28:34.505 --> 00:28:36.090
It's your call.

00:28:36.173 --> 00:28:38.426
Penny, there's
a combo syringe in the kit.

00:28:39.218 --> 00:28:41.012
<i>It's blue and white.
It'll knock her out.</i>

00:28:47.018 --> 00:28:48.060
[syringe hisses]

00:28:48.144 --> 00:28:51.188
It's okay.
Okay.

00:28:51.272 --> 00:28:53.858
Okay.
Yeah.

